column5: We had a local derby yesterday and guess who won!!! Hahaha, one fish caught, check out the weight haha.
Came right in time to buy the better half a bday present:) hahaha
i guess sometimes that's all you need to win a derby...congrats!

Thanks guys lol. We all had a good chuckle over that fish, and many jokes were shared haha. On a more serious note, any others here that fish river walleye? When water levels fluctuate i find its almost impossible fishing for 2-3 days. Anyone else notice this?
If it's the only fish caught, it doesn't need to be big to win...congrats  I once won $57 for a 1st place prize with a 35" musky
I remember the first ice fishing tourny I entered. Caught a perch that size and won a John Deere chain saw.  Sometimes,size dosent matter.LOL   Lew,that would be a PB for me.
Lol misfish,thats pretty awesome!  This is my 4th derby win. I think I'm ready to be that pro angler guy outa that animated video haha. And lew, a 35" musky would be a pb for me as well haha.
The way I see it you beat second place by 2 oz.    Art
Thanks! Heading up to fish rainy lake today, hopefully tie into some big walleye/pike!
